    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Audiences getting into the act in theaters is certainly not new. Fifteen years ago the audience determined what happened onstage in ''Edwin Drood.'' The musical, based on Charles Dickens's largely unfinished ''The Mystery of Edwin Drood,'' gave the audience a number of choices for the mystery's solution. The cast responded with appropriate closing action.</p>
        <p>HARRY THEMAL  Ardentown, Del.</p>
      </block>
